examples.en: Flags were waving in the breeze.
The flags were flying cheerfully in the breeze.
All nations fly their flags in front of the U.N.
Children waving flags greeted the Russian leader.
Flags flapped in the strong wind.
The flags were flapping in the breeze.
The soldiers' coffins were draped with American flags.
The street was decked with flags for the royal wedding.
The sports ground looked a treat, with all the flags flying.
The street was dressed out in flags when the victory was won.
Flags were flying at half-mast because of the death of the Premier.
Malaga was festooned with banners and flags in honour of the king's visit.
The government ordered that all flags should be flown at half mast (=halfway down the pole, in order to express public sadness at someone's death).
